ygData.subject: Re: Rambling a bit, was: Re: [EQ_women] Marriage question......
ygData.msgSnippet: Salutations Meleficent! Thanks, never know when one might come in handy . . . Brangvyne ...
ygData.messageBody:
Salutations Meleficent!

Thanks, never know when one might come in handy . . .

Brangvyne

--- Meleficent Ouverts <meleficent22@...> wrote:
>
> there is also a rude jester emote, i will look it up
> for you, LOL
> Melefante/30 ranger
> Brangvyne Accampo <brangvyne7@...>
> wrote:Salutations Christina!
> :o)
>
> << Basicly it's up to you to decide what is and is
> not
> acceptable in how you interact with people in the
> game. >>
>
> Yes, of course.
> :o)
> As my subject said I was only rambling a bit though.
> I'm afraid I tend to do that a lot.
> :o)
>
> << You can create your own emotes in the following
> way: /me slaps Joewoodelf That will make the game
> say
> Brangvyne slaps Joewoodelf >>
>
> Ah, cool, I knew you could create your own emotes,
> but
> didn't know how to set that up exactly.
> :o)
>
> << There are no easy answers to personal
> interactions,
> you need to figure that stuff out yourself. My
> advice
> is have fun and try to not unnecessarily hurt
> people's
> feelings, while at the same time ensuring people
> respect your boundaries. >>
>
> Yeah, your right of course. As I said just chatting
> more than anything. I am having fun, otherwise I
> wouldn't be playing the game or here talking about
> it,
> but I am aware that I tend to run on sometimes.
>
> :o)
> Brangvyne
>
> PS - If I'm "chatting" to much, or anything I say
> bothers anyone, or is just out of line or topic or
> whatever for the list someone is welcome to just
> tell
> me to shut up. I sometimes get carried away but I'm
> not offended if someone says enough already.
>
>
